1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the emerging technologies that will enable and define the 5G mobile communications standards, which is related to networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper mentions the need for higher data rates and reduced latency, which are related to information theory.
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the enhanced end-user quality-of-experience (QoE), which is related to multimedia.
4. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper mentions the lower energy consumption, which is related to hardware architecture.
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper discusses the measurement and test challenges for 5G systems, which can be related to computational engineering.
